Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible chronic kidney disease with tubular dysfunction. No evidence of urinary tract infection (negative nitrites, leukocytes, and hemoglobin). Recommend further nephrological evaluation and monitoring of renal function.
